electively unmaking it — the ICC campaign is the sharpest instance."},{"name":"Russia + China","bio":"The revisionists — one breaking rules by war, the other building parallel institutions by patience."},{"name":"The ICC / UN organs","bio":"The besieged referees — starved, defied, and now directly targeted, yet still the only game."},{"name":"The Global South swing states","bio":"The audience the contest plays to — their forum-shopping (BRICS, ICJ cases) is the order's real-time referendum."}],"bridge":"Getachew reframes what is being lost: the post-1945 order was not simply a Western gift under attack but a contested project that anticolonial worldmakers fought to universalize — self-determination, sovereign equality, the court no power stands above — and the 2026 assault (a P5 conquest normalized, the ICC targeted for dismantlement by the system's author) destroys precisely the parts the Global South spent decades winning. That is why the forum-shopping — BRICS, the ICJ cases, the withdrawal pressure resisted — is the real-time referendum: the audience deciding whether to defend an order that was partly theirs, or build the next one without its guarantors.","sources":[{"work":"Worldmaking after Empire: The Rise and Fall of Self-Determination","author":"Adom Getachew","year":"2019","note":"The anticolonial making of the order — the non-Eurocentric account of what the current assault unmakes."},{"work":"Governing the World: The History of an Idea","author":"Mark Mazower","year":"2012","note":"The long history of international order projects and their power politics."},{"work":"UN Charter / Rome Statute","author":"UN founding texts","year":"1945 / 1998","note":"The primary architecture under contest."}]}},{"id":"venezuela","cat":"military","region":"South America","subregion":"South America","name":"Venezuela — US Intervention / Remote Coercion","sub":"Maduro captured Jan 3 · US 'runs' oil · Rodríguez interim","domain":"Intervention / Occupation-by-Leverage","sev":"high","status":"volatile","since":"Sep 2025","esc":71,"lat":10.48,"lon":-66.9,"trend":"up","w14":false,"diplomacy_active":true,"esc_history":[71,70,71,71,71,71,71,71,71,71],"cas":"Op Absolute Resolve (Jan 3): Maduro security team largely killed; 32 Cuban soldiers killed; 7 US wounded","disp":"~8M Venezuelans emigrated since 2015 (3M+ in Colombia)","flag":"🇻🇪","note":"JUL 14-15 — THE TRANSITION GETS A TABLE: Govt (AN President Jorge Rodríguez, lead negotiator) and the OPPOSITION 2015-2020 legislature led by Dinorah Figuera agreed to launch a bilateral technical working group AUG 1 on electoral reforms — the first MUTUAL RECOGNITION between Venezuela's two parallel legislatures, US-backed (Rubio reposted the roadmap; 'strategic patience' 3-phase plan: stabilization→recovery→transition, elections LAST) · THE SPLIT: Machado + González were EXCLUDED — they convened an urgent meeting of Democratic Unitary Platform parties + Panama Manifesto signatories; Figuera's Washington-backed return blindsided Machado's own announced bid to lead negotiations · EARTHQUAKE TOLL FIRMED: the Jun 24 twin quakes killed 4,333 — the humanitarian emergency that delayed the talks · Jul 14: Johann Álvarez named new Chargé d'Affaires to the US · NEW THEATER (backfilled) · Jan 3 2026: Operation Absolute Resolve — US strikes on Caracas, Maduro + Cilia Flores captured, flown to NY on USS IWO JIMA (2h28m op) · VP Delcy Rodríguez sworn interim · Trump: 'We're going to run the country' · naval armada + tanker blockade remain · $2B stranded-crude export deal; first $500M sale ($300M to Caracas) · May: Alex Saab deported · Jun: Tren de Aragua chief Niño Guerrero killed in JOINT US-Venezuela op · Jun: earthquakes; Mexico aid via Rodríguez call · USER WARGAME LAYER: 44-asset pre-war order of battle (Ford CSG, Iwo Jima ARG, El Libertador Iran-UAV hub, S-300 IADS, Amuay/El Palito) staged into master KML · UPDATE (Jul): oil exports at 7-YEAR HIGH (~1M+ bpd, ~1% of global demand); CFR est. ~$8B exported Jan-Apr (a FLOOR — Trump admin shares no data, proceeds routed through Qatar account, transparency questioned by Congress); most goes to US Gulf refineries, then India · Cabello (Interior Min, $25M US bounty) given ultimatum: cooperate w/ transition or face arrest; Padrino ($15M bounty) holds military chain · Rodríguez wants $5B IMF Special Drawing Rights (blocked since 2019) — her key unmet ask; Rubio: Venezuela submits MONTHLY budget requests for State Dept approval · 621 of ~800 political prisoners released; ~400+ still held","leverage":[{"actor":"United States","asset":"Finance/legal HIGH (user matrix confirmed): blockade + OFAC licensing + oil-sale mechanism + offshore armada — coercion without occupation","str":"hi"},{"actor":"China","asset":"80-84% of Venezuela's oil exports (direct/indirect) + $10B debt — the unresolved contradiction in the $100B investment plan","str":"hi"},{"actor":"Rodríguez interim govt + generals","asset":"Colectivos/counterintel street presence; cooperation-for-survival (Saab handover, Guerrero op)","str":"md"},{"actor":"Russia + Iran","asset":"Diluent supply HIGH (naphtha/condensate); El Libertador UAV program; advisory footprint — degraded post-capture","str":"md"}],"gov":[{"src":"US Congress (CRS)","detail":"Administration notified Congress of 'non-international armed conflict' with cartels in Venezuela and beyond; War Powers resolutions (S.J.Res.83/90) considered, not passed"},{"src":"US Treasury TIC / DOJ","detail":"Maduro + Flores arraigned SDNY on narco-terrorism; $50M bounty claimed by US itself"},{"src":"China MFA / EU (Kallas)","detail":"China demands Maduro's immediate release ('blatant use of force against a sovereign state'); EU-minus-Hungary calls for restraint under UN Charter"},{"src":"UK House of Commons Library","detail":"Cuba confirmed 32 soldiers killed; large part of Maduro's security team killed; legality questioned under international law"}],"mil":"The kinetic phase predates our tracked window: Operation Absolute Resolve (Jan 3) — strikes across northern Venezuela suppressing air defenses while a Delta Force/CIA apprehension force took Maduro at Fuerte Tiuna, exfiltrating him aboard the USS Iwo Jima. Since W1 the model is remote coercion: the armada stays offshore, the tanker blockade holds, and strikes on 'drug boats' continue. The June joint US-Venezuela operation that killed Tren de Aragua leader Niño Guerrero shows the interim government now operationally cooperating with its coercer. USER OSINT: the staged 44-asset wargame layer maps the pre-war order of battle — including the Iwo Jima ARG that ultimately carried Maduro out, and El Libertador AB as the Iranian-assisted UAV hub (CAVIM/Mohajer line), the direct cross-link to the Iran theater.","pol":"Trump's 'we're going to run the country' remains policy: Rodríguez governs under threat ('pay a very big price'), opposition leader Machado is sidelined, and Crisis Group warns the transaction-not-transition model leaves the chavista security state intact minus its figurehead. The Donroe Doctrine framing — the right to intervene at will in the hemisphere — is the structural umbrella, with the AES's condemnation linking Pan-African and Latin American sovereignty pushback.","eco":"USER MATRICES (staged): PDVSA sold $17.52B abroad in 2024; Oct 2025 export baseline ~$1.63B/month at Brent, with China taking $1.34B of it — 80-84% of exports. US leverage concentrates in finance/legal (matrix: HIGH) not physical control, exactly matching the post-capture mechanism: blockade + licensing + managed oil sales ($500M sold, $300M remitted). Severe-discount scenario halves export value — the strangulation dial Washington controls.","assess":"Venezuela enters at 71 with a backfilled arc — high but stable, because the kinetic phase ended in January and what remains is an occupation-by-leverage in uneasy equilibrium. The user's pre-war wargame layer proved predictive (it mapped the Iwo Jima ARG that carried Maduro out) and now anchors the theater's