function openMethod(){
  const N=DB.length;
  const pipe=DB.filter(d=>d.pipeline&&d.pipeline.length).length;
  const hist=DB.filter(d=>d.history).length;
  const ctReal=DB.filter(d=>d.contested&&d.contested.claims&&d.contested.claims.length).length;
  const ctStub=DB.filter(d=>d.contested&&(!d.contested.claims||!d.contested.claims.length)).length;
  const seeded=DB.filter(d=>d.hist_real===false).length;
  const ext=DB.filter(d=>d.external&&d.external.length).length;
  const fresh={};DB.forEach(d=>{fresh[d.as_of||'—']=(fresh[d.as_of||'—']||0)+1;});
  const freshStr=Object.entries(fresh).sort((a,b)=>b[1]-a[1]).map(([k,v])=>v+' @ '+k).join(' · ');
  const tiers={};DB.forEach(d=>{tiers[d.tier]=(tiers[d.tier]||0)+1;});
  const sec=(t,b)=>`<div class="mth-sec"><div class="mth-h">${t}</div><div class="mth-b">${b}</div></div>`;
  board('⌘ METHODOLOGY · HOW THIS PLATFORM WORKS','',
    `<div class="intro-note" style="margin-bottom:14px">MERIDIAN's doctrine, definitions, and honesty rules — written down so the reader can audit the analyst. Coverage numbers below are computed live from the data, not typed by hand.</div>`
    +sec('THE LENS · LEVERAGE &amp; EXTRACTION',
      'Every theater is read through one question: <b>who extracts what from whom, who backs whom, and what does the backer take in return?</b> Conflicts are treated as economies with a war attached, not the reverse. This is why every theater carries a Leverage map, an Economic-leverage board, and (where a physical commodity flows) a mine→end-buyer Pipeline. Events matter when they move leverage; a battle that changes nothing on those boards is noise.')
    +sec('THE ESCALATION INDEX (0–100)',
      'A single analyst-assigned severity score per theater, comparable across the board. Approximate bands, assigned by judgment rather than formula: <b>90+</b> active mass-casualty war or systemic global risk (Sudan, Hormuz) · <b>~75–89</b> open armed conflict or acute crisis · <b>~55–75</b> contested/strategic-watch, violence present or latent · <b>&lt;~55</b> structural tension worth tracking. Boundary cases are placed by trajectory and spillover judgment, so a theater’s tier may sit one band off its raw number by design. The number encodes intensity + trajectory + spillover potential, weighted by human cost. It is a judgment, not a formula — the Method exists so the judgment is inspectable. Current tiers: '+Object.entries(tiers).map(([k,v])=>k+' '+v).join(' · ')+'.')
    +sec('SOURCE RELIABILITY · THREE TIERS',
      '<b style="color:var(--red)">DOCUMENTED</b> — multiple independent reputable sources, official records, satellite/OSINT, or on-record admission. Stated as fact.<br><b style="color:var(--amber)">ALLEGED-CREDIBLE</b> — serious single-source reporting, UN panel findings under dispute, intelligence leaks. Logged with attribution, never asserted.<br><b style="color:var(--violet)">DENIED</b> — claims the accused party rejects; the denial is part of the record. Every External-board flow and Pipeline node carries one of these badges. The rule: <b>allegations are logged, not asserted</b> — the reader always sees which tier a claim sits in.')
    +sec('DATA HONESTY RULES',
      '1. <b>Estimated history is labeled.</b> '+seeded+' of '+N+' theaters entered tracking recently; their 10-week curves are analyst back-estimates, flagged hist_real:false, segregated on the Movers board as "NOT YET TRACKABLE · EST" and excluded from delta rankings until two real weeks accumulate.<br>2. <b>"No change" is a valid sweep result.</b> News sweeps update only theaters that materially moved; unmoved theaters keep their prior note and get a verification stamp only when actually checked.<br>3. <b>Stubs stay honest.</b> '+ctStub+' Contested boards currently read "no narrative war identified" — a finding, not a gap. They are filled only when a real information war exists.<br>4. <b>as_of = last verified, not last edited.</b> Current freshness: '+freshStr+'.<br>5. <b>Week rollover.</b> esc_history is a 10-slot window whose last slot is the current week. At each new tracking week the window must be rolled (drop the oldest point, append the new week\u2019s label) via the rollweek maintenance script \u2014 slot labels may skip weeks when tracking pauses, and the label gap is kept visible rather than smoothed.')
    +sec('THE CONTESTED DOCTRINE',
      'Where narratives are weapons, the platform tracks the fight over the story as its own layer: each claim is logged with <b>who asserts it, who benefits, what the evidence shows, and a status verdict</b> (documented / contested / debunked). '+ctReal+' theaters carry live claim-vs-evidence boards. The test for inclusion: the narrative itself must be doing strategic work — recruiting, justifying intervention, laundering an atrocity, or moving markets.')
    +sec('BOARD ARCHITECTURE',
      'Theater cards hold the vertical detail (Overview, Gov-sources, Leverage, Econ, External, Contested, History, Assessment). Cross-theater boards hold the horizontal reads: <b>Systems</b> (networks spanning theaters — arms pipelines, gold laundering, evasion fleets), <b>Pipeline</b> ('+pipe+' theaters traced mine→end-buyer), <b>Patterns</b> (recurring leverage structures), <b>Blocs</b> (formal alignments), <b>Groups</b> (armed non-state actors), <b>Movers</b> (weekly deltas), <b>History</b> ('+hist+'/'+N+' theaters with roots+timeline+actor backstories), <b>Markets</b> (investment bridge), <b>Patrons</b> ('+ext+' theaters with external-actor boards). Nothing appears on a horizontal board that is not anchored in a theater record.')
    +sec('UPDATE WORKFLOW',
      'Each build: (1) news sweep against live reporting, prioritized by index and volatility; (2) patch only sourced, material changes — dated inline (e.g. "JUL 15 —"); (3) full engine validation: JS syntax check, stub-DOM runtime execution, board-render tests, data-integrity audit (no duplicate IDs, all required fields, esc_history length, coordinate sanity); (4) version bump with changelog. Fabricating updates to look busy corrupts the file — the discipline is that an honest "verified, unchanged" outranks an invented development.<br><b>Primary-statement monitoring:</b> head-of-state feeds (incl. Truth Social) are treated as primary sources with a verification gate \u2014 posts count only when confirmed via the public archive (trumpstruth.org) or independent wire reporting, because fabricated screenshots circulate constantly (PolitiFact-documented). Verified posts are logged as DOCUMENTED statements of intent, never as accomplished facts.')
    +sec('CHANGELOG \u00b7 RECENT BUILDS','<b>v56</b> Jul 17 sweep (6th-night strikes, blockade metrics, Fedorov firing); inline source links (refs); freshness-decay stamps; Watchlist TRIPPED tier \u00b7 <b>v56</b> cited-history standard complete 55/55 \u00b7 <b>v52</b> Asia histories \u00b7 <b>v51</b> week-rollover fix + rollweek tool + Europe/Eurasia histories \u00b7 <b>v50</b> full audit (7 sparkline desyncs fixed, tier-anchor doc corrected) \u00b7 <b>v48-49</b> Watchlist board + Middle East histories \u00b7 <b>v47</b> Markets live catalysts \u00b7 <b>v44-46</b> history layer 55/55, Africa citations, Jul 15-16 sweeps \u00b7 <b>v43</b> three dead boards recovered (Method/Systems/Patrons), board() arg fix')
    +sec('KNOWN LIMITS',
      'One analyst-AI pipeline, not a newsroom: single-point judgment on index scores; web-search source pool skews English-language; back-histories on newer theaters are estimates; freshness varies by theater (see stamps). The platform is a structured argument about the world, and its method is printed here so the argument can be checked.'));
}
